The '''Electronic Medical Records and Genomics Network''' (abbreviated the '''eMERGE Network''') is a consortium of American medical institutions dedicated to advancing the use of [[electronic medical record]]s for [[genomics]] research. It was established in 2007 and is funded by the [[National Human Genome Research Institute]] (NHGRI).<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://emerge.mc.vanderbilt.edu/about-emerge/ |title=welcome to eMerge |website=eMERGE website |access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref> eMERGE's Administrative Coordinating Center is located at [[Vanderbilt University Medical Center]].<ref>{{Cite journal |last=McCarty |first=Catherine A |last2=Chisholm |first2=Rex L |last3=Chute |first3=Christopher G |last4=Kullo |first4=Iftikhar J |last5=Jarvik |first5=Gail P |last6=Larson |first6=Eric B |last7=Li |first7=Rongling |last8=Masys |first8=Daniel R |last9=Ritchie |first9=Marylyn D |date=2011-01-26 |title=The eMERGE Network: A consortium of biorepositories linked to electronic medical records data for conducting genomic studies |journal=BMC Medical Genomics |language=En |volume=4 |issue=1 |pages=13 |doi=10.1186/1755-8794-4-13 |issn=1755-8794 |pmc=3038887 |pmid=21269473}}</ref>
eMERGE's first phase, known as eMERGE-I, began after the NHGRI awarded grants to five institutions: [[Group Health Cooperative]], [[Marshfield Clinic]], [[Mayo Clinic]], [[Northwestern University]], and [[Vanderbilt University]]. The second phase, eMERGE-II, began in August 2011, involving the same five sites as phase I plus two new ones: the [[Geisinger Clinic]] and [[Mount Sinai School of Medicine]].<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Gottesman |first=Omri |last2=Kuivaniemi |first2=Helena |last3=Tromp |first3=Gerard |last4=Faucett |first4=W. Andrew |last5=Li |first5=Rongling |last6=Manolio |first6=Teri A. |last7=Sanderson |first7=Saskia C. |last8=Kannry |first8=Joseph |last9=Zinberg |first9=Randi |date=2013-06-06 |title=The Electronic Medical Records and Genomics (eMERGE) Network: past, present and future |url=http://www.nature.com/articles/gim201372 |journal=Genetics in Medicine |language=En |volume=15 |issue=10 |pages=761–771 |doi=10.1038/gim.2013.72 |issn=1098-3600 |pmc=3795928 |pmid=23743551}}</ref>
